{"Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone": {"Harry James Potter, an 11-year-old boy, lives with his cruel relatives, Vernon and Petunia Dursley, and their spoiled son Dudley.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "Harry is unaware that he is a wizard, the son of famous wizards Lily and James Potter, who were killed by the dark wizard Lord Voldemort.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "However, Harry survived a deadly curse from Voldemort when he was a baby, and the dark wizard's spell backfired, leaving him nearly destroyed.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "Harry receives a mysterious letter from Rubeus Hagrid, the giant Keeper of Keys and Grounds at Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "Hagrid informs Harry that he has been accepted to Hogwarts and will be trained as a wizard.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "Harry boards the Hogwarts Express at King's Cross Station, accessing Platform 9\u00be through a magical barrier.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "He meets Ron Weasley and Hermione Granger on the train, forming a close-knit trio.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "At Hogwarts, Harry discovers that Nicolas Flamel created the Philosopher's Stone, a powerful object granting eternal life.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "The stone's existence attracts attention, and Harry, Ron, and Hermione begin to suspect that someone at Hogwarts is searching for it.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "They encounter the stone's protection in the form of a three-headed dog, Fluffy, and a series of magical obstacles designed to safeguard the stone.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "However, it is revealed that Quirrell is secretly working for Lord Voldemort, attempting to use the Philosopher's Stone's powers to regain a physical body and become immortal.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "Harry thwarts Voldemort's attempt to steal the stone, but Quirrell dies in the process.": {"questions": "", "types": ""}, "In the aftermath, Professor Dumbledore explains to Harry that his survival is due to the love his mother, Lily Potter, had for him.": {"questions": null, "types": null}, "This selfless love is a powerful magic that Voldemort cannot understand or overcome.": {"questions": null, "types": null}}}